{{Quote|I got this crazy healing ability. I can see the weak points in you like little broken red lines! I can see where you got wounded recently. Someone smack you during a sparring session? Bet it was Nihl. I could heal that hurt. Pour the Force into the place where the red lines intersect. Or&mdash;and here's a new idea&mdash;Maybe I could explode that point. Kill you. Interesting idea. Should we try?|Cade Skywalker to Darth Talon, after she had attacked him|<ref name="Legacy 16">[[Legacy (2006) 16|''Legacy'' (2006) 16]]</ref>}}
'''Dark transfer''', referred to by Darth Krayt as a '''Dark Transfer of Energy''', was a [[Force power/Legends|Force power]] that allowed the user to bring others back from the brink of [[Death/Legends|death]] or reawaken the dead by drawing upon the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] to [[Force healing/Legends|heal]]. [[Cade Skywalker]] was a notable user who instinctively used the ability without being taught. [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] [[Darth Krayt|Krayt]] learned it and succeeded in reviving himself from his own death.

==Description==
{{Quote|Cade, if the Force wills the princess die here, today, then who are ''you'' to stop her death?''"<br />"''How do you know it ''isn't'' the will of the Force that I save her?''"<br />"''Because to do it you must touch the dark side. You're not accepting the will of the Force&mdash;you're imposing your own!|Wolf Sazen and Cade Skywalker discuss the latter's intention to save Marasiah Fel|<ref name="Legacy 7">[[Legacy (2006) 7|''Legacy'' (2006) 7]]</ref>}}
Dark transfer<ref name="Campaign Guide" /><ref name="Legacy War 6">[[Legacy — War 6|''Legacy — War'' 6]]</ref> was a Force power that allowed the user to [[Force healing/Legends|heal]] someone who was on the brink of [[Death/Legends|death]]<ref name="Legacy 1" /> or when used to its full potential, one who had been slain<ref name="Campaign Guide" /> by drawing upon the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]<ref name="Legacy 7" /> and applying [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to [[Shatterpoint/Legends|shatterpoints]].<ref name="Legacy 45">[[Legacy (2006) 45|''Legacy'' (2006) 45]]</ref> Healing another through such a transfer was regarded by some [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] as imposing one's own will in defiance of the will of the Force.<ref name="Legacy 7" /> While tapping into the dark side to heal, arcs of [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]] appeared around the user, concentrated around their hands.<ref name="Legacy 1" /> The same lightning could be focused into the flaws of an object<ref name="Legacy 31" /> or person to destroy the user's target.<ref name="Legacy War 6" />

==Applications==
{{Quote|You see them, don't you, Skywalker&mdash;red lines of fire&mdash;the shatterpoints of your own tenuous existence. I needed to experience death to understand how you did it, but ''you'' showed me how to use this dark transfer of energy&mdash;how to ''heal''&hellip;and how to ''kill.|Darth Krayt, to Cade Skywalker|<ref name="Legacy War 6" />}}
At least one being, the Jedi learner [[Cade Skywalker]], manifested the ability rather than learning the technique from another. He first instinctively used his healing abilities<ref name="Legacy 7" /> when his [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]], [[Wolf Sazen]], was near death after [[Lightsaber duel/Legends|dueling]] [[Darth Nihl]].<ref name="Legacy 1" /> Skywalker would draw upon his rage and fear, touching the dark side in his refusal to let someone die.<ref name="Legacy 7" /> When healing another being through dark transfer, the user perceived wounds or areas of weakness as broken red lines. By pouring the Force into the intersections of those lines, the shatterpoints could be healed; however, the perception of those points could be used to cause harm instead when combined with Force lightning.<ref name="Legacy 16" /> The more damaged a body was, the harder it would be to use it to heal a target.<ref name="Legacy 31" />

==Users==
{{Quote|Healing me like you did was not something you were taught&mdash;you did that by instinct alone!''"<br />"''Like my instinct to tap into all the fear and rage I had in me? I walked on the dark side that day, Master.|Master Wolf Sazen and former pupil Cade Skywalker|<ref name="Legacy 7" />}}
[[Lord/Legends|Lord]] [[Karness Muur|Murr]] uncovered this technique during his life, and as such, [[Celeste Morne]] also knew how to apply the Force in this way.<ref name="Legacy 30" />

Around [[137 ABY]], [[Marasiah Fel]] was killed by Darth Nihl on [[Vendaxa/Legends|Vendaxa]] when she bodily blocked a lightsaber blow aimed at Cade Skywalker, who was frozen as he remembered the [[massacre at Ossus]].<ref name="Legacy 6">[[Legacy (2006) 6|''Legacy'' (2006) 6]]</ref> Rejecting Sazen's protests, Skywalker drew upon the dark side and returned Fel from death.<ref name="Legacy 7" />

[[Darth Krayt]] captured Skywalker in the hopes of healing the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] affliction that was slowly killing him. First, Krayt tested Skywalker's healing capabilities; Skywalker purged himself of lethal doses of [[Ixetal cilona/Legends|ixetal cilona]], but claimed that he could only heal himself. Krayt brought forward Skywalker's crewmates, [[Deliah Blue]] and [[Jariah Syn]], who had been infected with deadly [[Yorik-Kul|coral seeds]] by [[Darth Maladi]]. Although Skywalker had never previously healed two beings at once, he saved both of his friends from the seeds.<ref name="Legacy 15">[[Legacy (2006) 15|''Legacy'' (2006) 15]]</ref> Skywalker used his talent to injure [[Darth Talon]] with lightning after she attacked him for being impudent to Krayt. When Skywalker accepted Krayt's offer of lessons in using anger for power, he was ordered to heal the damage he caused to Talon.<ref name="Legacy 16" />

[[Celeste Morne]]'s [[rakghoul]]s infected Skywalker and [[Azlyn Rae]] with the [[Rakghoul plague/Legends|rakghoul plague]], which was only known to be curable with [[rakghoul serum]]. Morne's mention that it was like a virus inspired Skywalker to successfully use his healing ability on himself and Rae.  This successful healing surprised Muur as he observed what his “host” saw.<ref name="Legacy 28">[[Legacy (2006) 28|''Legacy'' (2006) 28]]</ref>

Morne had possessed the [[Muur Talisman]] for long years and was slowly losing her control to [[Karness Muur]]'s spirit within her. One of the first [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Dark Lords of the Sith]], Muur was gifted in healing through the dark side during his mortal lifetime, and he had [[Transfer essence|preserved his own essence]] in the talisman. Using Morne's body, Muur contacted Krayt and offered to heal the latter's Yuuzhan Vong infection, although it was part of Skywalker and Morne's ruse to lure Krayt to his death. [[Darth Wyyrlok (III)|Darth Wyyrlok]] affirmed to Krayt that the ancient Sith was said to know the art of dark side healing. At the meeting of the two dark lords, Muur began to heal Krayt; in the process, Krayt gained an initial understanding of how to utilize the ability.<ref name="Legacy 30">[[Legacy (2006) 30|''Legacy'' (2006) 30]]</ref>

After Morne's Force lightning mortally wounded Azlyn Rae,<ref name="Legacy 31">[[Legacy (2006) 31|''Legacy'' (2006) 31]]</ref> Skywalker ignored her desire to be allowed to die and forcibly sustained her life through dark transfer. He brought her to [[Droo Rawk]], a Force healer who was [[Marriage/Legends|married]] to Skywalker's uncle, [[Rawk|Nat Skywalker]], then known as "Bantha" Rawk. Cade secured the aid of his uncle and aunt by falsely claiming Rae did not want to die.<ref name="Legacy 34">[[Legacy (2006) 34|''Legacy'' (2006) 34]]</ref>

Cade Skywalker initially believed he could only utilize his talent for healing by drawing upon the dark side. The [[Force ghost/Legends|Force ghost]] of his ancestor [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] urged the young man to be at peace with himself,<ref name="Legacy 3">[[Legacy (2006) 3|''Legacy'' (2006) 3]]</ref> as did Sazen, so that Cade could heal with the [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light side]] instead of using the dark.<ref name="Legacy 7" /> When Cade attempted to use the power as he had before to save Blue from the [[Embrace of Pain]], he repeatedly failed and only caused her further pain.<ref name="Legacy 45" /> Sazen urged Skywalker to trust in the Force and the power of the light side to heal Blue instead of continuing his failed attempts with the dark. Skywalker was successful,<ref name="Legacy 46">[[Legacy (2006) 46|''Legacy'' (2006) 46]]</ref> and he used the light side again instead of dark transfer when he healed his [[Parent/Legends|mother]], [[Morrigan Corde]], after she was poisoned.<ref name="Legacy War 3">[[Legacy — War 3|''Legacy — War'' 3]]</ref>

Although Krayt had been murdered by Darth Wyrrlok, Krayt told Skywalker that experiencing death had given him an understanding of how to use dark transfer to heal or to kill; Krayt had revived himself from his own death. The Sith lord believed that Skywalker would understand his vision for the [[One Sith]] through experiencing the same death and self-revival. As such Krayt killed Cade Skywalker and resurrected him while showing a vision of the darkly glorious future of dark side supremacy if Cade summited. Skywalker rejected this ideal and used the opportunity to finally defeat Krayt while the [[Emperor/Legends|emperor]] was distracted. However, Krayt's [[Force ghost/Legends|Force ghost]] transcended his psychical form and taunted Skywalker, saying that he would either resurrect himself again or would claim Skywalker's body for his own through [[transfer essence]], which he had learned through [[Darth Andeddu]] and Karness Muur. Skywalker prevented Krayt from using either power by sending the Sith's corpse into [[Coruscant Prime/Legends|Coruscant's sun]].<ref name="Legacy War 6" />

